# Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Inviscid Flows over Axisymmetric Projectiles

This repository accompanies the paper:

> Physics-Informed Neural Networks for Inviscid Flows over Axisymmetric Projectiles, Miguel A. Escudero, Benoît G. Marinus, Karthik Depuru-Mohan, submitted to Computer Physics Communications, 2026.

The repository will contain the code used to train, evaluate, and post-process the physics-informed neural network models described in the paper. The implementation includes routines for:

- generating collocation and boundary points;
- defining the neural-network architecture and hard boundary-condition ansatz;
- evaluating axisymmetric Euler-equation residuals in axisymmetric coordinates;
- training with Adam and L-BFGS optimizers;
- comparing PINN predictions with CFD reference solutions;
- computing post-processing quantities such as pressure distributions, drag, and spectral error measures.

The repository is currently being organized for public release. The final version of the code will be uploaded during the review process and archived with a permanent DOI upon publication.
